- The string parameter `sentence` is a sentence consisting of words separated by a single space with no leading or trailing spaces.
- The words in the sentence consist of only uppercase and lowercase English letters.
- The sentence is circular if the last character of a word is equal to the first character of the next word, and the last character of the last word is equal to the first character of the first word.
- The boolean result is true if the sentence is circular, otherwise false.